# Playwright POM Architecture

- Keep page-object classes in `src/pages`.
- Keep specs in `tests/**/*.spec.ts`.
- Keep shared enums/test data in `src/fixtures/testData.ts`.
- Keep fixture wiring in `tests/fixtures/base.fixture.ts`.

## Interaction Boundary

- Element actions belong in page objects only:
  - `click`, `fill`, `selectOption`, `hover`, `check`, `uncheck`, `goto`.
- Specs must call page-object methods for interactions.
- Specs may use `expect(...)` on public page-object locators/state markers.

## Examples

```ts
// GOOD (spec)
await loginPage.loginAs(SauceUser.STANDARD);
await expect(inventoryPage.productsTitle).toBeVisible();
```

```ts
// BAD (spec)
await loginPage.usernameInput.fill(SauceUser.STANDARD);
await page.getByRole("button", { name: "Login" }).click();
```
